From 71a202539aad71e3d988398bff4f82c61a90bef0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 14:42:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Recon fog-of-war: hide enemy site composition until scouted,
 with overview toggle

Adds an opt-in recon intel-fog to the human player's map: a newly seen enemy
ground site shows as a targetable marker but its composition and threat/
detection rings stay hidden until it is attacked, scouted, or has a unit
destroyed (sticky per-site, enemy-only). AI planning and threat math are never
fogged (viewer=None). A transient 'Reveal fog of war' map overlay forces every
player-facing fog accessor to ground truth without altering saved state.

- known_for(viewer) leaf + discovered_by_player flag + save migration
  (TheaterGroundObject); recon_intel_fog campaign setting.
- Consumers gate at the edge: TgoJs, IADS connections, the human-facing threat
  zone overlay, and the ground-object dialog.
- reveal_discovered_sites/attacked_tgos_this_turn flip sites on engage.
- fog_revealed() overview flag + PUT /fog-of-war/reveal endpoint + a
  RevealFogToggle map overlay.
- Tests: recon intel-fog gate/setting/migration, reveal-on-engage, route.
